div.p:
And because there may be within the limits of your Diocess some peculiar or exempt Iurisdictions,
                     Par. 4 belonging either to your Dean, Dean and Chapter, Archdeacons, or to some Ecclesiastical or other persons: I do therefore desire that by such wayes and means as your Lordship shall conceive most proper, you do communicate this my Letter unto them, delivering unto every of them Copies of the same for their better Instruction;


and that you require them in My Name, that within their several Iurisdictions they also pursue the Advices and Directions before set down, as if the same had been given by a particular Letter unto them under my own hand.
